defaultThe Electrical Safety Roundtable was formed in response to widespread concern over poor promotion of competent registered electricians and a lack of Building Regulation enforcement. It is run by an independent secretariat; has 4 board members and is chaired by Chris Bielby, Chair of 
defaultTrustees at the Gas Safety Trust.  The roundtable aims to work collaboratively with industry and other relevant stakeholders to improve electrical safety in the home. 
